WEBVTT

1
00:02:00.955 --> 00:02:02.055
Movement.

2
00:02:03.455 --> 00:02:04.455
Two men.

3
00:02:06.055 --> 00:02:07.455
Approximately

4
00:02:09.955 --> 00:02:11.656
40 goats.

5
00:02:11.856 --> 00:02:15.356
They're not on anybody's side.
We don't have to shoot them.

6
00:02:16.556 --> 00:02:17.656
Egress?

7
00:02:18.456 --> 00:02:23.056
Primary over the top, secondary
down the road, tertiary to the river.

8
00:02:24.556 --> 00:02:27.556
No one can track you through the water
except a fish.

9
00:02:37.657 --> 00:02:40.457
Sarah's headed off to nursing school
next month.

10
00:02:41.557 --> 00:02:43.057
She sewed that herself.

11
00:02:43.357 --> 00:02:44.557
It's beautiful.

12
00:02:46.757 --> 00:02:48.958
You sure this is
a peacekeeping mission?

13
00:02:49.758 --> 00:02:52.458
Normally there isn't any peace
to start with.

14
00:02:54.458 --> 00:02:56.458
This shit's awful calm.

15
00:03:09.059 --> 00:03:10.335
-Not at these coordinates.
-Yes, sir.

16
00:03:10.359 --> 00:03:11.535
Go ahead and plot an alternate.

17
00:03:11.559 --> 00:03:12.759
Yes, sir.

18
00:03:13.159 --> 00:03:16.159
<i>Command Post, Command Post,
this is TS-129, over.</i>

19
00:03:16.859 --> 00:03:19.859
Sir, I have visual confirmation
of TS-129's current position.

20
00:03:20.159 --> 00:03:23.459
<i>Mission accomplished, en route to
extract site. Distance eight klicks. Over.</i>

21
00:03:23.659 --> 00:03:25.460
<i>Command Post, Command Post,
this is Viper.</i>

22
00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:28.160
<i>I have friendly forces moving
towards extraction point, over.</i>

23
00:03:29.660 --> 00:03:31.560
Heads up, our boys are coming through.

24
00:03:31.760 --> 00:03:33.460
<i>Viper, this is CP. Be advised,</i>

25
00:03:33.560 --> 00:03:36.760
<i>possible hostile forces approaching
TS-129 at their 12:00.</i>

26
00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:38.260
Call them out.

27
00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:39.660
Target.

28
00:03:40.460 --> 00:03:42.160
Sector Bravo, deep.

29
00:03:42.361 --> 00:03:44.461
Vehicle, belt-fed weapon.

30
00:03:44.761 --> 00:03:45.761
Range it.

31
00:03:50.161 --> 00:03:51.861
870 yards and closing.

32
00:03:52.861 --> 00:03:55.261
Wind, three-quarter value, push 2 left.

33
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:59.461
900 yards. Wide spot on the road.

34
00:04:01.162 --> 00:04:02.262
On target.

35
00:04:02.462 --> 00:04:03.662
Hold scope.

36
00:04:03.862 --> 00:04:05.162
Fire when ready.

37
00:04:08.762 --> 00:04:09.762
Hit.

38
00:04:15.662 --> 00:04:18.562
<i>Command Post, this is Viper.
Hostile threat down, over.</i>

39
00:04:18.762 --> 00:04:22.063
<i>Viper, this is Command Post.
We copy your traffic, over.</i>

40
00:04:32.463 --> 00:04:34.663
Call it in. It's time to go.

41
00:04:35.063 --> 00:04:36.939
Command Post, this is Viper.
Mission accomplished.

42
00:04:36.963 --> 00:04:37.964
-Packing up.
-Shit!

43
00:04:38.164 --> 00:04:41.364
<i>Viper, be advised larger hostile forces
approaching near sector Bravo.</i>

44
00:04:41.564 --> 00:04:43.764
Weren't supposed to be
hostiles that close!

45
00:04:51.064 --> 00:04:55.164
Crooked tree.
675, 30 miles an hour, three-mil lead.

46
00:05:00.865 --> 00:05:04.265
Position to machine gun.
900, three-quarter value.

47
00:05:04.865 --> 00:05:06.065
Fire when ready.

48
00:05:10.265 --> 00:05:13.765
<i>Jefe. 920. Three-quarter value.</i>

49
00:05:14.065 --> 00:05:16.966
-I see it, Donnie. I see it.
-Fire when ready.

50
00:05:25.866 --> 00:05:28.186
-They don't know where we are.
-But they might get lucky!

51
00:05:30.666 --> 00:05:32.666
<i>Command Post, Command Post,
this is Viper.</i>

52
00:05:32.866 --> 00:05:34.967
<i>Enemy forces
have been stopped. Break.</i>

53
00:05:35.267 --> 00:05:37.867
<i>Friendlies are continuing on
to extract point. Break.</i>

54
00:05:38.067 --> 00:05:41.767
<i>We're receiving small arms and
indirect fire from hostile troops. Break.</i>

55
00:05:44.667 --> 00:05:46.067
Command Post, do you read me?

56
00:05:46.267 --> 00:05:47.467
Shut it down.

57
00:05:47.567 --> 00:05:48.667
They're highly-trained men,

58
00:05:48.867 --> 00:05:51.468
eight kilometres inside a country
we are not supposed to be in.

59
00:05:51.768 --> 00:05:53.968
I'm sure they'll get out just fine.
Shut it down now.

60
00:05:54.168 --> 00:05:55.568
<i>Radio check. Do you read me?</i>

61
00:05:55.768 --> 00:05:57.768
-Okay, wrap it up. Let's go!
<i>-Do you read me?</i>

62
00:05:57.868 --> 00:06:00.388
-Pull out those tracks.
-Pull out those tracks and pack it up!

63
00:06:12.369 --> 00:06:14.369
Intelligence said
they didn't have air support!

64
00:06:14.569 --> 00:06:15.669
Call it in!

65
00:06:18.969 --> 00:06:21.669
Shit! The channel's down!

66
00:06:21.869 --> 00:06:22.969
That's impossible!

67
00:06:23.169 --> 00:06:24.469
The comm link's dead!

68
00:06:24.569 --> 00:06:27.269
They left us here.
Don't worry, we're getting home!

69
00:07:09.172 --> 00:07:10.272
Donnie?

70
00:07:12.872 --> 00:07:14.072
Donnie!

71
00:08:42.777 --> 00:08:44.177
Come on, boy!

72
00:08:45.977 --> 00:08:47.177
Come on, Sam!

73
00:08:48.977 --> 00:08:50.977
What're you doing, huh?
What're you doing?

74
00:08:51.177 --> 00:08:52.177
Come on.

75
00:08:52.377 --> 00:08:53.577
What? I got nothing.

76
00:08:53.677 --> 00:08:54.677
What?

77
00:08:55.778 --> 00:08:57.778
All right, come on, let's go. Let's go.

78
00:09:00.178 --> 00:09:01.578
That's a good boy.

79
00:09:14.779 --> 00:09:16.279
Good boy.

80
00:09:22.079 --> 00:09:24.779
{\an8}Well, let's see what lies
they're trying to sell us today.

81
00:09:28.879 --> 00:09:30.079
Here, boy.

82
00:09:31.279 --> 00:09:32.479
Good boy.

83
00:09:42.880 --> 00:09:46.380
Gunnery Sergeant Bob Lee Swagger.

84
00:09:46.680 --> 00:09:49.080
USMC, retired.

85
00:09:49.880 --> 00:09:51.481
He is the best there is.

86
00:09:51.781 --> 00:09:54.181
His last assignment went wrong.

87
00:09:54.481 --> 00:09:57.581
Put in unfriendly territory on a loan-out
and left as expendable.

88
00:09:57.881 --> 00:10:01.181
Opposing force sent an attack
helicopter and a hundred-man company.

89
00:10:01.381 --> 00:10:04.081
His best friend and spotter was killed.

90
00:10:04.281 --> 00:10:05.481
No official report.

91
00:10:05.681 --> 00:10:09.782
Ghost report says he inflicted
70 percent casualties, the rest fled.

92
00:10:09.982 --> 00:10:11.982
The agency asset
that left them there to die?

93
00:10:12.182 --> 00:10:15.182
Suddenly removed from
the face of the earth two weeks after.

94
00:10:15.582 --> 00:10:17.382
They never laid it at Bob Lee's feet.

95
00:10:17.582 --> 00:10:19.182
He retired a week later.

96
00:10:19.282 --> 00:10:22.282
I guess Bob Lee didn't think
he was expendable.

97
00:10:33.383 --> 00:10:34.783
Grows and shoots his own food.

98
00:10:34.983 --> 00:10:37.183
Yeah, he rarely ventures out at all.

99
00:10:37.383 --> 00:10:41.283
This is a man
with a history of duty and patriotism.

100
00:10:41.483 --> 00:10:44.983
-Not as punch lines, but as core beliefs.
-Aye.

101
00:10:45.383 --> 00:10:48.584
Some people don't know what to do
when their belief system collapses.

102
00:10:49.484 --> 00:10:51.184
Bob Lee is one of those.

103
00:11:01.284 --> 00:11:02.484
You sure, boy?

104
00:11:15.785 --> 00:11:19.185
Nope. I ain't buying. I don't want any.

105
00:11:19.485 --> 00:11:22.985
You guys turn around and go back
to wherever you came from.

106
00:11:23.986 --> 00:11:26.386
Bob Lee Swagger?

107
00:11:26.586 --> 00:11:28.486
My name is Colonel Isaac Johnson.

108
00:11:28.986 --> 00:11:30.186
You're a hard man to find.

109
00:11:30.286 --> 00:11:31.486
But not hard enough.

110
00:11:31.686 --> 00:11:33.186
Come a long way to see you.

111
00:11:33.586 --> 00:11:35.486
We have some business
needs your attention.

112
00:11:35.586 --> 00:11:37.262
You wanna use your low gear
going down the road

113
00:11:37.286 --> 00:11:38.286
or your brakes'll go.

114
00:11:38.586 --> 00:11:41.286
-Come here. Come here, boy.
-Don't do that.

115
00:11:42.487 --> 00:11:45.687
Come near the porch I didn't invite you,
you'd have to shoot the dog.

116
00:11:46.987 --> 00:11:48.387
That's a slow draw you got there.

117
00:11:48.587 --> 00:11:49.987
Sure you want to do that?

118
00:11:50.487 --> 00:11:52.063
Shoot a dog in this county
on a man's land,

119
00:11:52.087 --> 00:11:54.463
I'd bury you in the hill,
and tell the sheriff a month or two later.

120
00:11:54.487 --> 00:11:55.587
He understands.

121
00:11:57.087 --> 00:11:58.487
Take your hand off your weapon.

122
00:11:58.787 --> 00:11:59.787
Slowly.

123
00:12:00.188 --> 00:12:03.088
So the gunnery sergeant
doesn't have to bury you in the hill.

124
00:12:05.388 --> 00:12:07.088
I don't carry a gun.

125
00:12:11.488 --> 00:12:12.488
You know what that is?

126
00:12:12.788 --> 00:12:14.588
It's a Congressional Medal of Honour.

127
00:12:15.188 --> 00:12:16.688
They don't hand those out easy.

128
00:12:16.888 --> 00:12:17.988
Yours?

129
00:12:18.188 --> 00:12:19.489
Yeah.

130
00:12:19.589 --> 00:12:21.489
Your father had one, didn't he?

131
00:12:21.689 --> 00:12:23.189
What did you do?

132
00:12:23.389 --> 00:12:26.989
Something foolhardy.
Kept some other boys alive.

133
00:12:27.289 --> 00:12:28.989
Will you give me five minutes?

134
00:12:31.489 --> 00:12:33.089
Yeah, your dog stays outside.

135
00:12:34.489 --> 00:12:35.989
Come on, boy. Get in there.

136
00:12:37.490 --> 00:12:41.390
I need you to plan
a presidential assassination.

137
00:12:41.590 --> 00:12:42.690
Whose president?

138
00:12:42.890 --> 00:12:43.890
Ours.

139
00:12:45.590 --> 00:12:46.890
I didn't say "execute".

140
00:12:47.690 --> 00:12:48.790
Plan.

141
00:12:49.490 --> 00:12:51.490
So it can be stopped.

142
00:12:51.690 --> 00:12:55.190
There's gonna be an attempt on the life
of the President in the next two weeks.

143
00:12:55.391 --> 00:12:58.591
Code was broken
on an anonymous transmission.

144
00:13:00.591 --> 00:13:02.291
It was internal.

145
00:13:02.491 --> 00:13:04.791
We can't go to the usual agencies.

146
00:13:04.991 --> 00:13:07.691
The government itself
has been penetrated.

147
00:13:07.891 --> 00:13:13.091
The President has three
public engagements during that time.

148
00:13:13.391 --> 00:13:17.792
Baltimore, Philadelphia,
Washington, D.C.

149
00:13:18.092 --> 00:13:20.792
Standard Secret Service
protective cordon

150
00:13:21.192 --> 00:13:23.792
is out to 880 yards.

151
00:13:23.992 --> 00:13:28.492
But this intercept claims that the shot
will be taken from beyond a mile.

152
00:13:28.792 --> 00:13:31.592
We need you to scout,
tell us how you would do it,

153
00:13:32.092 --> 00:13:33.493
so we could stop it.

154
00:13:34.493 --> 00:13:38.893
I'm not entirely convinced
that a shot like this could be made.

155
00:13:40.493 --> 00:13:42.593
But let's not take the chance.

156
00:13:43.893 --> 00:13:45.993
Your longer shots
were never confirmed.

157
00:13:46.193 --> 00:13:47.993
That's because long shots
generally go places

158
00:13:48.193 --> 00:13:50.794
you wouldn't wanna have
to go afterwards to confirm them.

159
00:13:51.094 --> 00:13:53.594
Confirmation's a desk pogue's problem.

160
00:13:54.494 --> 00:13:56.694
You know what it takes
to make a shot at that range?

161
00:13:56.894 --> 00:13:58.334
Everything comes into play that far.

162
00:13:58.494 --> 00:14:01.494
Humidity, elevation, temperature,
wind, spindrift.

163
00:14:01.694 --> 00:14:03.134
There's a 6-to10-second flight time

164
00:14:03.194 --> 00:14:05.354
so you have to shoot
at where the target's going to be.

165
00:14:05.394 --> 00:14:08.394
Even the Coriolis effect,
the spin of the Earth, comes into play.

166
00:14:08.594 --> 00:14:10.871
President'll be wearing body armour.
That means a headshot,

167
00:14:10.895 --> 00:14:11.995
at over a mile.

168
00:14:12.295 --> 00:14:14.471
You believe there's a shooter involved
capable of making this shot?

169
00:14:14.495 --> 00:14:15.695
Yes.

170
00:14:15.895 --> 00:14:18.371
Well, then you got a real problem.
You need to find the shooter.

171
00:14:18.395 --> 00:14:20.695
That's being worked on
from another direction.

172
00:14:20.895 --> 00:14:22.495
We need you to do this.

173
00:14:22.695 --> 00:14:24.595
Don't really like the President much.

174
00:14:24.795 --> 00:14:26.595
Didn't like the one before
that much, either.

175
00:14:26.695 --> 00:14:28.496
You like the idea of the President?

176
00:14:28.896 --> 00:14:30.296
Living in a free country?

177
00:14:30.596 --> 00:14:32.896
Do we allow America
to be ruled by thugs?

178
00:14:33.096 --> 00:14:34.796
Sure, some years we do.

179
00:14:36.096 --> 00:14:38.796
I believe you stood before a flag

180
00:14:39.496 --> 00:14:40.696
and solemnly swore

181
00:14:41.696 --> 00:14:45.396
that you'd support and defend
the Constitution of the United States

182
00:14:45.596 --> 00:14:47.197
against all enemies,

183
00:14:47.397 --> 00:14:48.897
foreign and domestic.

184
00:14:49.197 --> 00:14:50.997
I think your five minutes is up.

185
00:15:00.497 --> 00:15:01.997
Listen to me, son.

186
00:15:04.197 --> 00:15:06.198
I don't want you to turn on the TV
next week

187
00:15:07.498 --> 00:15:09.698
and see the President dead,

188
00:15:09.898 --> 00:15:12.398
and know you could've done
something about it.

189
00:15:13.398 --> 00:15:15.398
Don't do that to yourself.

190
00:15:36.199 --> 00:15:37.899
Is that the new one?

191
00:15:38.199 --> 00:15:39.299
The truck.

192
00:15:40.899 --> 00:15:42.300
You got the big engine in there?

193
00:15:42.400 --> 00:15:45.800
Wow, look at that, huh? Eight-litre V8.

194
00:15:46.100 --> 00:15:49.700
Thing's so big, EPA doesn't even bother
to give you the gas mileage for it.

195
00:15:49.900 --> 00:15:51.400
You mind if I take a picture?

196
00:15:53.300 --> 00:15:54.800
This is beautiful.

197
00:15:59.300 --> 00:16:01.901
Someone will be at this number
night or day.

198
00:16:07.301 --> 00:16:09.801
You see what he did?
He didn't need a photo of the engine.

199
00:16:10.001 --> 00:16:12.201
No, he doesn't give a rat's ass
about the engine.

200
00:16:12.401 --> 00:16:13.801
He's trained in counterintel.

201
00:16:14.001 --> 00:16:16.201
Backed up far enough
to take a picture of the plates.

202
00:16:16.401 --> 00:16:17.801
This is our guy.

203
00:16:18.002 --> 00:16:19.402
I thought he turned you down.

204
00:16:19.602 --> 00:16:21.902
He said yes. He just doesn't know it yet.

205
00:17:36.806 --> 00:17:38.806
1,760's a mile.

206
00:17:39.706 --> 00:17:43.206
It's a far piece, Sam.
Think the President ought to worry?

207
00:18:15.208 --> 00:18:16.808
Yeah, I think he better worry.

208
00:18:31.609 --> 00:18:33.309
Yeah, he'll be fine.

209
00:18:34.509 --> 00:18:38.309
Just feed him once a day. Read him
a few ballistics tables if he looks Ionely.

210
00:18:38.509 --> 00:18:39.709
Yep. I'm out.

211
00:18:41.609 --> 00:18:43.009
Come here, buddy.

212
00:18:43.809 --> 00:18:45.009
Okay.

213
00:18:45.610 --> 00:18:49.010
Think you'll be able to tough it out
without me for a couple days?

214
00:18:50.010 --> 00:18:51.010
Yeah.

215
00:20:18.115 --> 00:20:20.215
<i>This is Command Post.
What's your status? Over.</i>

216
00:20:20.415 --> 00:20:22.115
Yeah, we're finishing up here on 6th.

217
00:20:22.315 --> 00:20:25.015
<i>Roger that. We copy.
Checkpoint down, over.</i>

218
00:20:38.016 --> 00:20:42.616
Before you stands Independence Hall,
the birthplace of the United States

219
00:20:43.016 --> 00:20:45.716
and one of the most important buildings
in American history.

220
00:20:46.316 --> 00:20:48.016
Built in 1732...

221
00:20:48.216 --> 00:20:50.216
Keep a visual eye on 72nd...

222
00:20:50.416 --> 00:20:52.792
...both the Declaration of Independence
and the U.S. Constitution

223
00:20:52.816 --> 00:20:54.917
were debated and signed here.

224
00:21:03.617 --> 00:21:04.617
Out of the three cities,

225
00:21:04.717 --> 00:21:07.517
there's only one with
a reasonably high chance of success.

226
00:21:08.317 --> 00:21:09.557
There was no room in Baltimore.

227
00:21:09.617 --> 00:21:11.193
Street isn't wide enough to correct
for the windage,

228
00:21:11.217 --> 00:21:12.817
buildings are in the way.

229
00:21:13.118 --> 00:21:14.518
D.C.'s a pure suicide mission.

230
00:21:14.718 --> 00:21:16.894
I mean, unless you're sure
your shooter's interested in 70 virgins

231
00:21:16.918 --> 00:21:18.094
waiting for him in the afterlife,

232
00:21:18.118 --> 00:21:19.518
I'd rule that out.

233
00:21:19.718 --> 00:21:21.118
Shot's got to be taken from Philly.

234
00:21:21.618 --> 00:21:23.418
<i>From beyond 1,800 yards, though.</i>

235
00:21:23.618 --> 00:21:25.018
<i>It's one of six possible locations,</i>

236
00:21:25.218 --> 00:21:28.018
<i>approximately five storeys
above the President's location.</i>

237
00:21:28.718 --> 00:21:31.218
<i>Flight time of the bullet that distance
is five to six seconds.</i>

238
00:21:31.419 --> 00:21:32.795
<i>They'll have to wait
till he takes the podium,</i>

239
00:21:32.819 --> 00:21:34.319
<i>several lines into his speech.</i>

240
00:21:34.419 --> 00:21:37.119
<i>That way he'd be completely static,
obviously at his most exposed.</i>

241
00:21:37.419 --> 00:21:39.219
<i>Shot requires a large-calibre weapon.</i>

242
00:21:39.319 --> 00:21:41.919
<i>Expect the bullet to be handmade,
bronzed alloy turned on a lathe.</i>

243
00:21:42.319 --> 00:21:43.495
<i>Slightly lower ballistics coefficient,</i>

244
00:21:43.519 --> 00:21:44.619
touch more slippery.

245
00:21:44.819 --> 00:21:46.219
Least that's what I'd do.

246
00:21:46.419 --> 00:21:48.619
You can kill him from that far away?

247
00:21:50.720 --> 00:21:52.796
Mile and a half, the bullet's
going to strike with more energy

248
00:21:52.820 --> 00:21:53.980
than a.44 Magnum point blank.

249
00:21:54.020 --> 00:21:55.720
Yeah, I think you can kill him.

250
00:21:56.320 --> 00:21:57.520
