729
01:04:30.158 --> 01:04:31.659
I'm not gonna ask you again.

730
01:04:33.259 --> 01:04:34.959
Take your hat off, asshole!

731
01:04:44.059 --> 01:04:46.759
Get on the ground!
Get your ass on the ground!

732
01:05:20.261 --> 01:05:21.461
Hey, how's it going?

733
01:05:23.261 --> 01:05:24.461
Hey, John.

734
01:05:48.063 --> 01:05:49.163
-Hey, Ed?
-Yeah.

735
01:05:49.363 --> 01:05:51.163
You got that Stevens file
we wanted back?

736
01:05:53.763 --> 01:05:56.763
How badly do you want to know?
Because this will get you fired.

737
01:05:57.263 --> 01:06:02.663
Well, I have to go before
the Office of Professional Responsibility

738
01:06:03.063 --> 01:06:04.864
in 45 minutes for a review.

739
01:06:05.164 --> 01:06:08.064
I'm gonna get fired anyway.
I'm done worrying about that.

740
01:06:09.364 --> 01:06:11.264
What do you think?

741
01:06:12.064 --> 01:06:14.364
I think that CNN got the tapes
before we did,

742
01:06:14.564 --> 01:06:16.764
already edited together
to show the angles.

743
01:06:17.064 --> 01:06:18.064
Who delivered them?

744
01:06:18.264 --> 01:06:21.464
An unnamed agency
who will never confirm or deny.

745
01:06:21.764 --> 01:06:23.665
They denied, which is a...

746
01:06:26.265 --> 01:06:29.365
Which is a confirmation of sorts.

747
01:06:29.565 --> 01:06:31.265
Of what?

748
01:06:31.465 --> 01:06:34.865
That you are asking questions
way outside your pay grade.

749
01:06:35.265 --> 01:06:36.305
Oh, come on, just tell me.

750
01:06:36.365 --> 01:06:38.005
You don't want to be here
for that review.

751
01:06:38.065 --> 01:06:41.466
They don't have to stop at firing you.
They can charge you and hold you.

752
01:06:50.466 --> 01:06:53.966
The ASAC's job
comes with Delta clearance.

753
01:06:57.166 --> 01:06:58.466
-Thank you.
-Go.

754
01:07:05.667 --> 01:07:07.567
This is a copy of a chat room transcript.

755
01:07:07.767 --> 01:07:10.767
These guys talk about everything.
I didn't give it much thought at the time.

756
01:07:10.967 --> 01:07:13.267
We just traced it to a doughnut shop
with free WiFi.

757
01:07:13.567 --> 01:07:16.167
But this,
this is a Delta-level clearance request

758
01:07:16.367 --> 01:07:19.068
out of the FBI field office in Philadelphia
seven minutes ago.

759
01:07:19.368 --> 01:07:21.768
Funny thing,
Google Maps puts the doughnut shop

760
01:07:22.068 --> 01:07:24.468
only three blocks away
from the field office.

761
01:07:24.668 --> 01:07:27.568
There's only one guy who met
with Swagger before he disappeared.

762
01:07:27.768 --> 01:07:28.968
He lives in Philly.

763
01:07:29.268 --> 01:07:30.668
And he works for the FBI.

764
01:07:31.968 --> 01:07:33.268
Nicholas Memphis.

765
01:07:33.768 --> 01:07:37.069
...really strange company.
Contracts with a lot of the Fortune 500.

766
01:07:37.369 --> 01:07:39.969
Offices in Virginia, Delaware,
registered in Panama.

767
01:07:40.269 --> 01:07:41.989
They own a boat
that's flagged out of Libya.

768
01:07:42.169 --> 01:07:43.245
<i>They're definitely not government,</i>

769
01:07:43.269 --> 01:07:45.869
<i>but they have high ex-military contacts
like you wouldn't believe.</i>

770
01:07:46.169 --> 01:07:47.269
<i>These are contractors.</i>

771
01:07:47.369 --> 01:07:49.769
<i>I can't tell
what this company does, but...</i>

772
01:07:51.569 --> 01:07:52.669
Hey.

773
01:07:52.769 --> 01:07:53.869
Hey, hey, hey!

774
01:07:58.870 --> 01:07:59.870
<i>Memphis?</i>

775
01:08:00.070 --> 01:08:01.070
<i>Memphis!</i>

776
01:08:08.370 --> 01:08:10.070
For a man who didn't know much,

777
01:08:10.270 --> 01:08:13.371
you sure took a long,
painful time to tell it.

778
01:08:13.671 --> 01:08:15.271
Get him some water.

779
01:08:24.371 --> 01:08:25.471
Good.

780
01:08:36.072 --> 01:08:37.172
Got to pee yet?

781
01:08:37.472 --> 01:08:39.172
Got to flush them drugs
out of your system.

782
01:08:39.272 --> 01:08:41.553
Look awful suspicious
if you were to go and shoot yourself

783
01:08:41.772 --> 01:08:43.872
pumped full of the same shit
the agency uses.

784
01:08:44.072 --> 01:08:45.972
I'm not going to shoot myself.

785
01:08:46.872 --> 01:08:47.872
Sure you will.

786
01:08:48.972 --> 01:08:50.373
Take him out. Get him ready.

787
01:08:50.573 --> 01:08:51.573
No!

788
01:08:57.273 --> 01:08:58.373
That's my gun.

789
01:08:58.473 --> 01:08:59.573
Yeah.

790
01:09:00.073 --> 01:09:02.373
You wrote a real touching
suicide note, too.

791
01:09:02.673 --> 01:09:04.873
All overwrought with guilt
about your mistakes.

792
01:09:12.074 --> 01:09:13.474
Quit your struggling.

793
01:09:17.174 --> 01:09:20.774
This thing works.
It's not the first time we've used it.

794
01:09:25.374 --> 01:09:27.075
Russo. Russo!

795
01:09:27.275 --> 01:09:28.875
Davis, get out here!

796
01:09:33.775 --> 01:09:35.775
What is the goddamn hold-up?

797
01:10:13.477 --> 01:10:16.577
Don't kill me, please!
Don't kill me! I believe you!

798
01:10:16.777 --> 01:10:17.777
Kill you?

799
01:10:17.977 --> 01:10:20.577
Had enough chances.
I wanted you dead, you'd be dead.

800
01:10:21.778 --> 01:10:24.478
What kind of asshole'd
think up a thing like this?

801
01:10:32.878 --> 01:10:35.978
Not bad with a poodle shooter
and a makeshift silencer, huh?

802
01:10:37.478 --> 01:10:39.478
Help me toss these boys in the water?

803
01:10:39.678 --> 01:10:41.879
You set me up and you used me as bait!

804
01:10:42.179 --> 01:10:44.779
You think? Flushed them out, didn't it?

805
01:10:45.079 --> 01:10:45.979
I was kind of hoping to keep one alive,

806
01:10:46.079 --> 01:10:48.079
but they were
kind of determined to kill you.

807
01:10:48.379 --> 01:10:50.479
You can hire a good lawyer,
and I'll call the Bureau.

808
01:10:50.679 --> 01:10:52.479
They can work out some kind of deal.

809
01:10:53.579 --> 01:10:56.419
This is explainable. You can prove
that you didn't shoot the Archbishop.

810
01:10:56.479 --> 01:10:57.639
I don't think you understand.

811
01:10:57.779 --> 01:10:58.880
These boys killed my dog.

812
01:11:01.880 --> 01:11:04.780
Hey, this is the 21st century.
You can't go to war with these people.

813
01:11:04.980 --> 01:11:06.480
In the end, the law is all...

814
01:11:06.680 --> 01:11:09.180
In the end,
the law'll never catch and hold them.

815
01:11:09.480 --> 01:11:10.756
In a year or two,
they'll be back in business.

816
01:11:10.780 --> 01:11:13.180
New names, new messenger boys,
same old story.

817
01:11:13.480 --> 01:11:14.580
And I'll be dead.

818
01:11:14.880 --> 01:11:16.680
It's gonna be
some hard, hairy work, Pork.

819
01:11:16.880 --> 01:11:19.057
There's gonna be more shooting,
and more people are gonna die.

820
01:11:19.081 --> 01:11:22.181
Now, I didn't start it, but be sure as hell
I mean to see it through.

821
01:11:22.381 --> 01:11:24.781
So you get it straight. You in or you out?

822
01:11:28.181 --> 01:11:29.541
You know, I missed a meeting today

823
01:11:29.681 --> 01:11:32.981
where I was going to get fired
for unprofessional conduct

824
01:11:33.181 --> 01:11:35.982
because I was kidnapped by people
that don't exist.

825
01:11:40.882 --> 01:11:42.182
I'll take his legs.

826
01:11:42.382 --> 01:11:43.782
It's a good call, Pork.

827
01:11:44.582 --> 01:11:47.282
You're trying to tell me
a rookie FBI agent

828
01:11:47.482 --> 01:11:49.082
overpowered and killed
the three of them?

829
01:11:49.282 --> 01:11:50.382
No.

830
01:11:51.082 --> 01:11:54.883
They were shot from a distance
of about 200 yards.

831
01:11:56.883 --> 01:11:58.083
With a.22.

832
01:12:00.083 --> 01:12:02.183
-Swagger's alive.
-Yes.

833
01:12:02.383 --> 01:12:03.783
And that young kid,

834
01:12:04.183 --> 01:12:05.683
FBI Agent

835
01:12:08.183 --> 01:12:09.383
Nick Memphis,

836
01:12:09.483 --> 01:12:13.084
who managed to pry out
a Delta-level clearance,

837
01:12:13.384 --> 01:12:16.984
hasn't come back to the office
and is out there with him.

838
01:12:19.284 --> 01:12:20.284
What?

839
01:12:20.384 --> 01:12:22.484
I just went over
Swagger's financials again.

840
01:12:22.984 --> 01:12:26.484
Once a year, he sent flowers
to someone with his Visa card.

841
01:12:26.784 --> 01:12:29.084
I cracked the FTD database,
got an address.

842
01:12:29.284 --> 01:12:32.385
Donnie Fenn's widow.
Anniversary of his death.

843
01:12:32.685 --> 01:12:33.861
She went back to using
her maiden name,

844
01:12:33.885 --> 01:12:36.085
which is why we missed it the first time.

845
01:12:37.385 --> 01:12:39.161
She's maybe the only person
in the entire world

846
01:12:39.185 --> 01:12:41.225
that would believe anything
that Swagger had to say.

847
01:12:41.385 --> 01:12:44.585
Look. Keene City, Kentucky.

848
01:12:44.885 --> 01:12:46.485
It's just within driving range.

849
01:12:47.485 --> 01:12:50.086
-What are you waiting for? Take the jet.
-All right.

850
01:12:57.986 --> 01:12:59.586
We've given Swagger a new war,

851
01:13:00.186 --> 01:13:01.586
he's found a new spotter.

852
01:13:02.986 --> 01:13:04.486
This is about to get worse.

853
01:13:33.688 --> 01:13:35.288
I think we're here.

854
01:13:36.488 --> 01:13:37.588
Hey. Swagger.

855
01:13:42.088 --> 01:13:43.488
I think we're here.

856
01:13:46.689 --> 01:13:48.689
Welcome to Tennessee.

857
01:13:48.889 --> 01:13:50.889
Patron state of shooting stuff.

858
01:13:53.289 --> 01:13:54.689
Hey, who is this guy?

859
01:13:54.789 --> 01:13:58.189
This guy was the greatest gunsmith
east of the Mississippi. He's a legend.

860
01:13:58.489 --> 01:14:00.609
He knows more about guns
and the people who shoot them

861
01:14:00.689 --> 01:14:01.689
than Smith & Wesson.

862
01:14:01.789 --> 01:14:04.366
Don't really matter anymore. He knew
we were coming the last three miles.

863
01:14:04.390 --> 01:14:05.666
-You mind your manners.
-All right.

864
01:14:05.690 --> 01:14:09.090
You boys come a long way.
What you looking for?

865
01:14:09.490 --> 01:14:10.590
Wisdom.

866
01:14:12.690 --> 01:14:14.290
You come to the wrong place.

867
01:14:14.390 --> 01:14:15.590
Maybe.

868
01:14:15.790 --> 01:14:17.566
Say a man wanted to fire a bullet
from one rifle

869
01:14:17.590 --> 01:14:19.090
and have it match exactly to another.

870
01:14:19.190 --> 01:14:20.590
Could that be done?

871
01:14:20.790 --> 01:14:21.791
Take a seat.

872
01:14:22.691 --> 01:14:23.791
Have a chair, son.

873
01:14:28.191 --> 01:14:31.891
If you could get a bullet that had been
shot clean through the first rifle,

874
01:14:32.291 --> 01:14:33.691
could make the grooves match.

875
01:14:33.791 --> 01:14:35.991
Kind of thing ain't been done
in a long time, though.

876
01:14:36.291 --> 01:14:37.867
The bullet that was taken
out of the Archbishop

877
01:14:37.891 --> 01:14:39.391
was completely mangled on impact.

878
01:14:39.591 --> 01:14:41.692
FBI match was metallurgical.

879
01:14:41.992 --> 01:14:42.992
Thank you, Mother.

880
01:14:43.192 --> 01:14:45.668
Yeah, but you couldn't guarantee that
going in, so they had to be sure.

881
01:14:45.692 --> 01:14:47.992
And I still can't figure out
how they could be.

882
01:14:51.092 --> 01:14:52.592
-Good coffee?
-Yep.

883
01:14:54.692 --> 01:14:57.692
Look on your left, there.
Second shelf down.

884
01:14:58.693 --> 01:15:00.793
Red leather spine.

885
01:15:01.093 --> 01:15:03.893
Written by a guy named Schofeld.

886
01:15:05.193 --> 01:15:08.893
Put it there 15 years ago.
Don't figure it's moved since then.

887
01:15:28.794 --> 01:15:30.894
Yeah. Paper patching.

888
01:15:31.194 --> 01:15:34.194
State of the art. 1870s Africa.

889
01:15:34.394 --> 01:15:35.495
Paper-wrapped bullet.

890
01:15:35.795 --> 01:15:38.095
No metal on metal
going down the barrel.

891
01:15:38.395 --> 01:15:41.295
Grooves would match.
Paper unwinds at the muzzle.

892
01:15:41.495 --> 01:15:43.395
Leaves no traces when it hits.

893
01:15:43.695 --> 01:15:47.095
Interesting question, though.
Hope I satisfied you.

894
01:15:47.295 --> 01:15:48.495
I got another one.

895
01:15:49.395 --> 01:15:50.395
I thought you might.

896
01:15:50.595 --> 01:15:53.395
Suppose I was looking for a man
to make a 2,200-yard cold-bore shot.

897
01:15:53.696 --> 01:15:55.296
Who's alive that could do that?

898
01:15:55.896 --> 01:15:59.896
Seems I heard about a shot like that
being made not too long ago.

899
01:16:00.196 --> 01:16:03.196
Said the guy's name
was Bob Lee Swagger.

900
01:16:03.396 --> 01:16:05.496
Never met the man,
so I wouldn't know him.

901
01:16:05.696 --> 01:16:07.096
Yeah, they said that, all right.

902
01:16:07.196 --> 01:16:10.796
They also said
that artificial sweeteners were safe,

903
01:16:11.896 --> 01:16:14.397
and WMDs were in Iraq,

904
01:16:14.697 --> 01:16:17.197
and Anna Nicole married for love!

905
01:16:19.197 --> 01:16:20.997
Would've been
a bad job to take, though.

906
01:16:21.197 --> 01:16:22.197
How come?

907
01:16:22.397 --> 01:16:24.897
Whoever took that shot's
probably dead now.

908
01:16:25.097 --> 01:16:26.897
That's how a conspiracy works.

909
01:16:27.097 --> 01:16:30.598
Them boys on the grassy knoll,
they were dead within three hours.

910
01:16:30.798 --> 01:16:34.598
Buried in the damn desert.
Unmarked graves out past Terlingua.

911
01:16:34.898 --> 01:16:36.198
And you know this for a fact?

912
01:16:36.398 --> 01:16:37.998
Still got the shovel.

913
01:16:40.298 --> 01:16:42.098
Sake of argument,
somebody other than him?

914
01:16:42.298 --> 01:16:43.698
There was a guy in Russia.

915
01:16:43.898 --> 01:16:45.498
They locked his ass up.

916
01:16:46.298 --> 01:16:48.899
Another one in France.
I know he's dead.

917
01:16:49.999 --> 01:16:51.699
There was one guy,

918
01:16:51.899 --> 01:16:54.099
but he don't shoot no more.

919
01:16:54.599 --> 01:16:57.199
A brutal son of a bitch.

920
01:16:57.399 --> 01:17:00.399
Most boys shoot to kill.
He'd shoot to wound,

921
01:17:01.299 --> 01:17:02.899
wait till his friends come to help,

922
01:17:03.299 --> 01:17:04.499
kill them too.

923
01:17:04.699 --> 01:17:06.699
Turned one target into four.

924
01:17:07.600 --> 01:17:11.100
Men, women, children.
Killed them by the hundreds.

925
01:17:11.500 --> 01:17:13.600
The other side wanted him. Bad.

926
01:17:13.800 --> 01:17:18.900
Finally narrowed his hide down
to an abandoned six-storey building.

927
01:17:20.300 --> 01:17:22.100
They quit the subtle tactics.

928
01:17:22.300 --> 01:17:24.900
They called in an artillery strike.

929
01:17:25.100 --> 01:17:26.901
Levelled a square block.

930
01:17:27.101 --> 01:17:29.101
Brought the building down on his ass.

931
01:17:29.401 --> 01:17:31.701
Some say he crawled out of there.

932
01:17:31.901 --> 01:17:33.501
Some say he died.

933
01:17:33.801 --> 01:17:35.601
Never heard from him no more.

934
01:17:36.401 --> 01:17:37.701
Fuck me.

935
01:17:38.001 --> 01:17:39.001
What?

936
01:17:39.101 --> 01:17:40.501
I met the son of a bitch.

937
01:17:45.002 --> 01:17:47.902
Yeah. The world ain't what it seems,
is it, Gunnie?

938
01:17:49.002 --> 01:17:50.102
No, sir.

939
01:17:50.302 --> 01:17:51.802
You keep that in mind.

940
01:17:51.902 --> 01:17:53.702
The moment you think you got it figured,

941
01:17:53.902 --> 01:17:54.902
you're wrong.

942
01:17:58.902 --> 01:17:59.902
He got a name?

943
01:18:05.503 --> 01:18:06.903
<i>Hey, it's me, Nick.</i>

944
01:18:07.003 --> 01:18:09.803
Do you have any idea
how much trouble you're in?

945
01:18:10.703 --> 01:18:12.603
-Yeah.
<i>-Are you okay? Nick, where are you?</i>

946
01:18:12.803 --> 01:18:14.003
It's better I don't tell you.

947
01:18:14.903 --> 01:18:17.203
Look, do you have a pen?

948
01:18:17.403 --> 01:18:19.603
<i>I need you to find someone.
Mikhaylo Sczerbiak.</i>

949
01:18:19.903 --> 01:18:20.903
-Yeah.
<i>-You got it?</i>

950
01:18:21.004 --> 01:18:22.004
I got it.

951
01:18:22.204 --> 01:18:23.904
Man, this is hard to spell.

952
01:18:30.204 --> 01:18:33.204
Swagger is going to go
with what he knows.

953
01:18:33.404 --> 01:18:35.604
He'll try to track the shooter.

954
01:18:35.804 --> 01:18:37.304
He won't get far that way.

955
01:18:37.504 --> 01:18:38.904
Yes, he will.

956
01:18:39.104 --> 01:18:41.105
-How's that?
-We're going to help him.

957
01:18:41.205 --> 01:18:44.105
Sometimes to catch a wolf,
you need to tie the bait to a tree.

958
01:18:51.505 --> 01:18:53.105
And what happens to the bait?

959
01:18:54.705 --> 01:18:56.005
Hard to say.

960
01:18:57.105 --> 01:18:59.606
But that's the nature of being the bait.

961
01:19:12.706 --> 01:19:15.006
<i>-Hey, it's Nick. Did you find him?</i>
-He's in Virginia.

962
01:19:16.206 --> 01:19:18.207
An end we thought was tied up

963
01:19:18.507 --> 01:19:19.607
came untied.

964
01:19:20.607 --> 01:19:22.207
Meaning, Colonel?

965
01:19:22.307 --> 01:19:24.007
Swagger is still alive.

966
01:19:27.607 --> 01:19:28.807
Oh, my.

967
01:19:29.607 --> 01:19:34.007
I need to land a transport plane
without a customs check.

968
01:19:35.908 --> 01:19:39.408
I'm certain I don't want to know,
but what's on the plane?

969
01:19:41.308 --> 01:19:43.008
Crew we used in Ethiopia.

970
01:19:43.208 --> 01:19:46.108
Twenty-four good, hard men.

971
01:19:46.308 --> 01:19:48.308
Weapons and gear.

972
01:19:48.508 --> 01:19:50.008
Only 24?

973
01:19:51.508 --> 01:19:52.808
Do kill him.

974
01:19:54.609 --> 01:19:56.509
No loose ends this time.

975
01:19:57.509 --> 01:19:58.909
Night, Colonel.

976
01:20:00.409 --> 01:20:01.509
Good night, Senator.

977
01:20:20.410 --> 01:20:21.410
Hello?

978
01:20:23.610 --> 01:20:25.010
Someone there?

979
01:21:01.412 --> 01:21:02.412
Now look.

980
01:21:03.112 --> 01:21:04.912
Look what you've done now.

981
01:21:08.313 --> 01:21:09.613
Give me that.

982
01:21:09.813 --> 01:21:12.613
I don't want you to hurt yourself. Okay?

983
01:21:21.313 --> 01:21:23.113
Where's your boyfriend?

984
01:21:25.414 --> 01:21:26.914
{\an8}What if it's a trap?

985
01:21:27.314 --> 01:21:28.714
Oh, it's a trap.

986
01:21:28.914 --> 01:21:31.114
Guaranteed. Every time.

987
01:21:33.114 --> 01:21:34.714
Question is, for whom?

988
01:21:36.314 --> 01:21:38.014
-You got your list, right?
-Yep.

989
01:21:38.214 --> 01:21:40.414
All right, you make sure you stick to it.

990
01:22:08.516 --> 01:22:09.516
Let's go.

991
01:22:15.016 --> 01:22:16.916
Okay, so what are these for again?

992
01:22:17.716 --> 01:22:19.416
Tear gas is going to be on my remote.

993
01:22:19.616 --> 01:22:21.117
Right.

994
01:22:21.217 --> 01:22:25.217
Napalm on the first floor.
Pipe bombs on the rest of them.

995
01:22:25.517 --> 01:22:29.417
Gotta be very careful with these.
It's got a 15-foot kill radius.

996
01:22:29.717 --> 01:22:31.817
So what exactly
are we getting ready for?

997
01:22:32.017 --> 01:22:33.317
For as much as we can be.

998
01:22:46.618 --> 01:22:48.718
All right, you got
four enemy combatants.

999
01:22:48.918 --> 01:22:50.518
Take them one by one.

1000
01:22:50.718 --> 01:22:52.558
Keep shooting.
Don't let anything distract you.

1001
01:23:01.319 --> 01:23:02.319
Fuck!

1002
01:23:04.619 --> 01:23:06.919
Didn't I say
don't let anything distract you?

1003
01:23:07.219 --> 01:23:09.519
Slow is smooth, smooth is fast.
Let's see it.

1004
01:23:25.820 --> 01:23:27.220
No. No.

1005
01:23:27.920 --> 01:23:29.620
It's just you and me, baby.

1006
01:23:29.720 --> 01:23:30.720
No!

1007
01:23:33.920 --> 01:23:35.321
You got three guards.

1008
01:23:36.321 --> 01:23:37.621
One at your 2:00,

1009
01:23:39.121 --> 01:23:40.121
12:00

1010
01:23:41.621 --> 01:23:42.621
and 10:00.

1011
01:23:51.321 --> 01:23:52.321
Danger close. 2:00,

1012
01:23:52.521 --> 01:23:53.622
<i>fifty yards.</i>

1013
01:24:57.025 --> 01:24:58.125
<i>You got one right on you.</i>

1014
01:24:58.625 --> 01:24:59.625
20 yards and closing.

1015
01:25:50.328 --> 01:25:51.628
Go check the perimeter.

1016
01:25:52.128 --> 01:25:53.628
And tell the others to stay alert.

1017
01:25:53.728 --> 01:25:55.328
I'm on it. Right away, sir.

1018
01:26:29.630 --> 01:26:31.310
Swagger, you got one above you
on the roof.

1019
01:26:49.831 --> 01:26:51.031
You killed all three?

1020
01:26:52.031 --> 01:26:53.331
There were four.

1021
01:26:54.331 --> 01:26:57.632
I want Johnson's real name.
I want to know who he works for.

1022
01:26:57.932 --> 01:26:59.808
I want to know why it was worth
going through that much effort

1023
01:26:59.832 --> 01:27:01.232
to kill the Archbishop.

1024
01:27:02.232 --> 01:27:03.632
Aren't you the one that shot him?

1025
01:27:03.932 --> 01:27:05.832
And if I don't know any of those things?

1026
01:27:06.032 --> 01:27:07.192
Then you're of no worth to me

1027
01:27:07.232 --> 01:27:09.232
and I might as well shoot you now
and leave.

1028
01:27:13.632 --> 01:27:15.933
Johnson's had a lot of names.

1029
01:27:16.133 --> 01:27:19.733
Don't know one's any more real
than the next.

1030
01:27:20.033 --> 01:27:21.633
Knowing would only be dangerous.

1031
01:27:23.333 --> 01:27:24.833
He's ex-army.

1032
01:27:25.033 --> 01:27:27.333
Pretty sure he was a full-bird colonel.

1033
01:27:30.733 --> 01:27:31.833
Go on.

1034
01:27:33.633 --> 01:27:36.334
They came for me,
like they came for you.

1035
01:27:37.634 --> 01:27:39.934
Recruitment for a single job.

1036
01:27:41.634 --> 01:27:43.034
They like the wounded.

1037
01:27:44.234 --> 01:27:45.834
Easier to use

1038
01:27:47.034 --> 01:27:48.934
and then throw away
when you are done.

1039
01:27:50.334 --> 01:27:52.234
Timmons, you, me...

1040
01:27:55.035 --> 01:27:59.735
Once you've been a wolf, it's hard
to be staked down like a goat.

1041
01:28:01.035 --> 01:28:05.535
This is just one dead man
talking to another.

1042
01:28:06.935 --> 01:28:08.135
And the Archbishop?

1043
01:28:09.835 --> 01:28:13.536
You want to take all suspicions away
when you shoot someone,

1044
01:28:13.936 --> 01:28:16.236
wait till he's standing
next to the President.

1045
01:28:17.736 --> 01:28:19.136
What was he going to say?

1046
01:28:20.236 --> 01:28:21.436
The truth.

1047
01:28:21.736 --> 01:28:25.036
That nothing, no matter how horrible,

1048
01:28:25.336 --> 01:28:28.636
ever really happens
without the approval of the government.

1049
01:28:29.036 --> 01:28:30.837
Over there, and here.

1050
01:28:33.037 --> 01:28:34.737
The problem isn't the doing.

1051
01:28:36.337 --> 01:28:38.337
It's the people in power having to admit

1052
01:28:38.937 --> 01:28:39.937
that they knew.

1053
01:28:41.737 --> 01:28:44.437
The prisoners are tortured
at Abu Ghraib,

1054
01:28:44.637 --> 01:28:46.737
and only the underlings go to jail.

1055
01:28:47.537 --> 01:28:49.138
Their bosses knew.

1056
01:28:49.338 --> 01:28:51.338
We know their bosses knew.

1057
01:28:51.538 --> 01:28:52.638
But you don't say it.

1058
01:28:52.938 --> 01:28:54.538
What exactly happened in Africa?

1059
01:28:54.638 --> 01:28:57.038
Somehow the villagers didn't think

1060
01:28:57.338 --> 01:28:59.238
that an oil pipeline

1061
01:28:59.838 --> 01:29:02.538
was a good enough reason
to move their village

1062
01:29:02.838 --> 01:29:06.039
to a place
where the spirit gods didn't exist.

1063
01:29:06.239 --> 01:29:07.239
Drink?

1064
01:29:07.339 --> 01:29:08.615
So they asked them all nicely to move

1065
01:29:08.639 --> 01:29:10.115
and when they didn't,
they just killed them all?

1066
01:29:10.139 --> 01:29:11.139
No.

1067
01:29:11.239 --> 01:29:12.439
They didn't ask.

1068
01:29:12.839 --> 01:29:14.239
They just killed them.

1069
01:29:14.339 --> 01:29:15.339
AII.

1070
01:29:15.539 --> 01:29:18.439
So the next village
won't need to be asked.

1071
01:29:18.639 --> 01:29:19.839
They'll just go.

1072
01:29:31.740 --> 01:29:35.740
There is a mass grave with 400 bodies,

1073
01:29:36.140 --> 01:29:39.640
men, women, children,

1074
01:29:39.940 --> 01:29:44.341
under the oil pumping station
10 kilometres over the Eritrean border.

1075
01:29:46.241 --> 01:29:47.641
You should know.

1076
01:29:47.841 --> 01:29:51.741
You covered the retreat
of the contractors who did the job.

1077
01:29:53.241 --> 01:29:55.841
Of course, you weren't supposed
to survive that, either.

1078
01:30:05.142 --> 01:30:06.242
Who runs Johnson?

1079
01:30:06.442 --> 01:30:08.742
A senator. From Montana, I think.

1080
01:30:10.342 --> 01:30:11.942
You don't get it.

1081
01:30:12.442 --> 01:30:14.442
There is no head to cut off.

1082
01:30:15.742 --> 01:30:17.442
It's a conglomerate.

1083
01:30:18.142 --> 01:30:20.743
If one of them betrays the principles

1084
01:30:22.443 --> 01:30:24.543
of the accrual of money and power,

1085
01:30:25.843 --> 01:30:27.443
the others betray him.

1086
01:30:28.643 --> 01:30:30.043
What it is

1087
01:30:32.343 --> 01:30:34.543
is human weakness.

1088
01:30:36.043 --> 01:30:38.844
You can't kill that with a gun.

1089
01:30:46.744 --> 01:30:47.744
Swagger.

1090
01:30:47.944 --> 01:30:48.944
<i>Swagger.</i>

1091
01:30:49.144 --> 01:30:51.744
<i>You got to get out of there.
They're everywhere.</i>

1092
01:30:52.744 --> 01:30:55.644
Had to keep you till they got here.

1093
01:30:57.145 --> 01:31:00.345
Lying wasn't going to hold you.

1094
01:31:01.245 --> 01:31:02.745
You would have known.

1095
01:31:07.845 --> 01:31:11.045
By the way, they've got your woman.

1096
01:31:14.145 --> 01:31:15.146
<i>Swagger.</i>

1097
01:31:15.446 --> 01:31:18.646
They're 20 yards and closing.
You got to get out of there.

1098
01:31:20.646 --> 01:31:22.446
-Bug out. Go to hide two.
<i>-Roger that.</i>

1099
01:31:54.548 --> 01:31:56.148
Swagger, I'm in position two.

1100
01:31:57.148 --> 01:31:58.268
You got to get out of there.

1101
01:31:58.348 --> 01:31:59.748
<i>-They're all over the place.</i>
-Hey!

1102
01:32:00.448 --> 01:32:01.748
<i>Calm down.</i>

1103
01:32:01.948 --> 01:32:04.348
Blow the pipe bombs outside on my call,
okay? You got it?

1104
01:32:04.748 --> 01:32:06.448
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, I got it.

1105
01:32:14.149 --> 01:32:15.149
Listen very carefully.

1106
01:32:15.249 --> 01:32:16.749
On my one, you blow the pipe bombs,

1107
01:32:16.949 --> 01:32:18.049
<i>then the gas.</i>

1108
01:32:19.049 --> 01:32:20.649
Three, two, one...

1109
01:32:50.651 --> 01:32:51.851
Hit it. Hit the napalm.

1110
01:33:46.954 --> 01:33:47.954
Swagger!

1111
01:33:55.154 --> 01:33:56.354
You got it.

1112
01:34:07.755 --> 01:34:08.855
<i>Swagger!</i>

1113
01:34:11.355 --> 01:34:12.855
<i>Swagger!</i>

1114
01:34:13.655 --> 01:34:14.855
Swagger!

1115
01:34:21.556 --> 01:34:23.316
You got to bug out
on my go behind that barn.

1116
01:34:23.456 --> 01:34:24.456
Okay.

1117
01:34:24.556 --> 01:34:25.556
-You ready?
-Yeah.

1118
01:34:25.856 --> 01:34:26.856
Go!

1119
01:34:30.356 --> 01:34:31.356
Come on!

1120
01:34:59.758 --> 01:35:01.134
You got to gun it to that tree line.

1121
01:35:01.158 --> 01:35:02.158
What?

1122
01:35:02.358 --> 01:35:04.318
You got five shots left.
Gotta draw that bird out.

1123
01:35:04.358 --> 01:35:05.558
Okay. Okay.

1124
01:35:05.758 --> 01:35:07.558
-On my cover, all right?
-Okay.

1125
01:35:09.358 --> 01:35:10.358
All right, go!

1126
01:35:23.759 --> 01:35:25.259
Pull up! Pull up!

1127
01:35:41.360 --> 01:35:42.360
Time to go!

1128
01:36:00.261 --> 01:36:01.261
Let me take a look.

1129
01:36:01.661 --> 01:36:02.661
Not right now.

1130
01:36:03.161 --> 01:36:04.361
Morning, beautiful.

1131
01:36:04.661 --> 01:36:06.761
-See this weird shootout in Virginia?
-Sir...

1132
01:36:06.961 --> 01:36:11.062
Shells everywhere, helicopter remnants,
blood. No bodies, though, right?

1133
01:36:11.362 --> 01:36:14.862
And they get fingerprints
off the cartridge cases.

1134
01:36:15.062 --> 01:36:18.162
First set positively IDed
as Bob Lee Swagger.

1135
01:36:20.062 --> 01:36:23.362
Second set belongs
to Special Agent Nick Memphis

1136
01:36:24.062 --> 01:36:25.362
of the FBI.

1137
01:36:25.762 --> 01:36:27.262
What? That's gotta be wrong.

1138
01:36:30.663 --> 01:36:33.963
Now, the only reasonable question
to ask after that is,

1139
01:36:36.463 --> 01:36:37.663
what the fuck is going on?

1140
01:36:43.663 --> 01:36:44.963
Great shot!

1141
01:36:48.564 --> 01:36:50.964
-All yours, Dan!
-Good shooting!

1142
01:36:51.164 --> 01:36:54.364
I'm beginning to think that you were
the wrong man for the job.

1143
01:36:56.064 --> 01:36:57.464
Think what you want.

1144
01:37:00.164 --> 01:37:03.864
It appears we misjudged
the gunnery sergeant.

1145
01:37:05.865 --> 01:37:07.765
There's always a confused soul

1146
01:37:07.965 --> 01:37:10.465
that thinks that one man
can make a difference.

1147
01:37:11.665 --> 01:37:14.665
And you have to kill him
to convince him otherwise.

1148
01:37:17.265 --> 01:37:19.165
That's the hassle with democracy.

1149
01:37:19.665 --> 01:37:20.665
Pull!

1150
01:37:35.066 --> 01:37:36.866
...fire under their asses,
you understand me?

1151
01:37:37.066 --> 01:37:38.566
We need those results now.

1152
01:37:38.766 --> 01:37:41.242
Anna, you guys, you take the team...
Anna! ...to the roadhouse.

1153
01:37:41.266 --> 01:37:43.667
Okay, I don't care who it is right now.
I don't give...

1154
01:37:43.967 --> 01:37:46.967
Guys! We got Memphis on the line.

1155
01:37:47.167 --> 01:37:48.367
Start a trace.

1156
01:37:49.367 --> 01:37:50.867
Got it. I'm on it.

1157
01:37:51.067 --> 01:37:53.167
Nick. Hey, it's Howard here.
How are you?

1158
01:37:53.567 --> 01:37:56.567
Things have gotten a little complicated.
I got Bob Lee Swagger in custody.

1159
01:37:57.667 --> 01:37:59.567
Yeah, turns out he's not dead, Howard.

1160
01:37:59.767 --> 01:38:02.268
Yeah, I know. Word of that possibility
had begun to reach us.

1161
01:38:03.168 --> 01:38:04.268
Got him.

1162
01:38:04.468 --> 01:38:06.244
Were you in a gunfight
in Virginia last night?

1163
01:38:06.268 --> 01:38:08.868
Like I said,
things have gotten a little complicated.

1164
01:38:09.068 --> 01:38:13.268
Well, obviously the best thing for you
would be to bring him in, right?

1165
01:38:13.568 --> 01:38:15.368
Oh, no. I can't do that.

1166
01:38:15.568 --> 01:38:16.568
Why?

1167
01:38:16.668 --> 01:38:18.868
It's gotten too deep.
It's not clear who can be trusted.

1168
01:38:19.569 --> 01:38:21.769
-But we're the FBI, son.
<i>-Yeah, I know.</i>

1169
01:38:22.269 --> 01:38:23.369
Yeah, I'll keep in touch.

1170
01:38:23.769 --> 01:38:24.769
Oh, Nick, wait...

1171
01:38:24.969 --> 01:38:26.769
Son of a bitch.

1172
01:38:26.969 --> 01:38:28.089
-Did we get that?
-Got him.

1173
01:38:28.169 --> 01:38:29.245
-Let's move.
-They're on an interstate

1174
01:38:29.269 --> 01:38:31.369
-outside Bozeman, Montana.
-Let's move!

1175
01:38:37.169 --> 01:38:38.170
This is Swagger.

1176
01:38:38.370 --> 01:38:40.246
<i>-Colonel Johnson here.</i>
-Figured you'd be listening.

1177
01:38:40.270 --> 01:38:42.570
-It appears you have nowhere to go.
<i>-Colonel?</i>

1178
01:38:43.170 --> 01:38:44.270
If it is "Colonel"?

1179
01:38:44.470 --> 01:38:45.570
It is.

1180
01:38:47.170 --> 01:38:50.170
-I have something you want.
<i>-Well, it seems so do I.</i>

1181
01:38:53.270 --> 01:38:57.771
<i>Over the Eritrean border,
there is a mass grave with 400 bodies.</i>

1182
01:38:58.171 --> 01:39:00.771
<i>Men, women, children.</i>

1183
01:39:02.071 --> 01:39:03.947
Tell you what, I'll give it to you
and we'll call it even.

1184
01:39:03.971 --> 01:39:05.491
I just want someone there I can trust.

1185
01:39:05.671 --> 01:39:08.071
I'm amenable.
Who do you have in mind?

1186
01:39:08.271 --> 01:39:10.071
How about that guy from U2
with the glasses?

1187
01:39:10.271 --> 01:39:12.571
Friend of Nelson Mandela and all.
He seems trustworthy.

1188
01:39:12.771 --> 01:39:14.672
Bono? You want them to get Bono?

1189
01:39:14.972 --> 01:39:18.072
My colleague's questioning
my choice. Okay,

1190
01:39:18.372 --> 01:39:21.672
I see how that could be a tough
problem. You know, last minute and all.

1191
01:39:22.772 --> 01:39:24.572
How about six-term senator
Charles Meachum

1192
01:39:24.872 --> 01:39:26.072
<i>from Montana?</i>

1193
01:39:26.372 --> 01:39:28.972
<i>Seems like a pretty good
second choice, don't you think?</i>

1194
01:39:30.872 --> 01:39:32.072
I don't think so.

1195
01:39:32.272 --> 01:39:34.973
I'm gonna provide you
with two numbers, then we'll talk.

1196
01:39:35.173 --> 01:39:37.673
Point 732. Point 648.

1197
01:39:38.373 --> 01:39:39.473
And what the hell is that?

1198
01:39:39.673 --> 01:39:42.833
Those are the last three digits, down to
a few metres of latitude and longitude,

1199
01:39:42.973 --> 01:39:44.773
of an oil pipeline pumping station
in Eritrea

1200
01:39:45.073 --> 01:39:46.273
<i>with 400 bodies underneath.</i>

1201
01:39:47.073 --> 01:39:48.173
Where are we meeting?

1202
01:39:49.873 --> 01:39:51.974
Somewhere I can see you,

1203
01:39:53.074 --> 01:39:55.774
coming from a goddamn long way off.

1204
01:41:04.377 --> 01:41:05.678
Where's your boy?

1205
01:41:20.078 --> 01:41:21.678
Well, I'm here.

1206
01:41:30.479 --> 01:41:31.479
He's here.

1207
01:41:31.679 --> 01:41:32.879
Look, look, look.

1208
01:41:33.879 --> 01:41:35.779
There's your boy.
There's your boy, baby.

1209
01:41:44.480 --> 01:41:46.580
Come on, come on. Look, look. Look up.

1210
01:41:56.880 --> 01:41:58.080
Okay.

1211
01:42:41.683 --> 01:42:43.283
I think I broke a rib!

1212
01:42:45.083 --> 01:42:46.183
Don't move!

1213
01:42:46.583 --> 01:42:47.983
Is there anybody else?

1214
01:42:48.683 --> 01:42:49.683
No.

1215
01:43:16.585 --> 01:43:19.185
He head-shoots me, spasm kills her!

1216
01:43:20.485 --> 01:43:22.385
You got no shot!

1217
01:43:22.585 --> 01:43:25.885
No shot, Swagger!
You hear that, Swagger?

1218
01:43:28.785 --> 01:43:30.485
You got no shot!

1219
01:43:31.185 --> 01:43:33.786
What are you gonna do? Come on!

1220
01:43:42.886 --> 01:43:44.486
It's over for you, buddy!

1221
01:43:49.586 --> 01:43:52.087
No shot! Okay, fuck him.

1222
01:44:06.287 --> 01:44:07.687
Not bad!

1223
01:44:07.887 --> 01:44:10.088
Pretty good! He went for the shot.

1224
01:44:12.588 --> 01:44:13.588
Christ.

1225
01:44:31.489 --> 01:44:32.489
How can we help you?

1226
01:44:32.789 --> 01:44:34.789
Guest at the motel last night
gave me $100

1227
01:44:34.989 --> 01:44:36.789
to bring this by here at 3:00 p.m.

1228
01:44:40.489 --> 01:44:41.589
Let's move!

1229
01:45:10.491 --> 01:45:11.591
You all right?

1230
01:45:12.391 --> 01:45:13.391
Yeah.

1231
01:45:23.692 --> 01:45:24.692
Search him.

1232
01:45:24.792 --> 01:45:26.292
I don't carry a weapon,

1233
01:45:29.392 --> 01:45:30.492
ordinarily.

